cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with recognizing actions from still images, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new spatial SPN method for modeling the spatial relationship and high-order correlations of body parts, which involves machine learning techniques. Hence, it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper uses unsupervised learning to discover a set of parts in image collections, which could also place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category.
